### REST API Testing File
### You can use this file with the "REST Client" extension in VS Code
### 1. Install "REST Client" by Huachao Mao in your VS Code Extensions
### 2. Click "Send Request" above each endpoint

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api/v1

### ---------------------------------------------------------
### 1. Public Endpoints
### ---------------------------------------------------------

### Get all products (with optional pagination/filters)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?page=1

###

### Get a single product (Replace the ID below with a real product ID from the above request)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/REPLACE_WITH_PRODUCT_ID

### ---------------------------------------------------------
### 2. Authentication
### ---------------------------------------------------------

### Login User (Replace with an email/password you registered via the website)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Extract the token from the login response to use in protected routes below
### Copy the "token" value from the response and replace "YOUR_TOKEN_HERE" below.

### ---------------------------------------------------------
### 3. Protected Endpoints (Require valid JWT Token)
### ---------------------------------------------------------

### Get Authenticated User Profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

###

### Submit a New Order
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "products": [
    {
      "product": "REPLACE_WITH_PRODUCT_ID",
      "quantity": 2
    }
  ],
  "totalAmount": 1999
}
